          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to make permanent the reduction in the adjusted gross income threshold that must be exceeded before a taxpayer is allowed to claim an itemized deduction for medical expenses. (In 2017, the threshold was temporarily reduced from 10% to 7.5% for 2017 and 2018. This bill makes the 7.5% threshold permanent.)</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2018-11-14T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2018-11-26T17:13:05Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
        </item>
